data.text:
Taylor County

Taylor county is located in northwest Florida. Taylor county has 1,043.30 square miles of land area and 188.90 square miles of water area. As of 2010-2014, the total Taylor county population is 22,690, which has grown 17.83% since 2000. The population growth rate is lower than the state average rate of 21.14% and is much higher than the national average rate of 11.61%. Taylor county median household income is $36,907 in 2010-2014 and has grown by 22.89% since 2000. The income growth rate is higher than the state average rate of 21.62% and is lower than the national average rate of 27.36%. Taylor county median house value is $84,000 in 2010-2014 and has grown by 27.27% since 2000. The house value growth rate is much lower than the state average rate of 48.06% and is much lower than the national average rate of 46.91%. As a reference, the national Consumer Price Index (CPI) inflation rate for the same period is 26.63%. On average, the public school district that covers Taylor county is close to the state average in quality. The Taylor county area codes are 352, 850.
